configset  GLOBAL  token_lifetime = [VALUE]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
configset listname token_lifetime = [VALUE]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value : 7
Data Type     : integer
Variable Group: access, token
Password Notes: Visible only with password. Set with global password. 
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset GLOBAL token_lifetime = 4


The number of days that a token will be allowed to live without being
acknowledged (either approved or rejected).  Tokens existing longer
than this many days are deleted at every daily trigger.


See Also:
   help configset dup_lifetime
   help configset latchkey_lifetime
   help configset log_lifetime
   help configset post_limits
   help configset session_lifetime
   help configset triggers

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
